{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Adrian Beria Blog","author":"Adrian Beria"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3f244ea7-ddd2-50c5-a7e2-6d53db123785","excerpt":"What are we gonna do Setting up Redux can be a struggle for some people and the objective of this post is to make it simple! Which libraries…","html":"<h2>What are we gonna do</h2>\n<p>Setting up Redux can be a struggle for some people and the objective of this post is to make it simple! Which libraries to install, the recomended structure and how to implement it, then finally finishing with a step by step formula for this.</p>\n<h2>Installing dependencies</h2>\n<p>For an alredy created project:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add redux react-redux</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you’re doing some async</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add axios redux-thunk</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Project structure</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>src</p>\n<ul>\n<li>actions</li>\n<li>api</li>\n<li>components</li>\n<li>pages</li>\n<li>reducers</li>\n<li>store</li>\n<li>types</li>\n<li>App.js</li>\n<li>index.js</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each folder will have an index.js file inside.</p>\n<h2>Types</h2>\n<p>Inside the types folder we add our constants</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/setting-redux-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 544px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 21.507352941176467%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/setting-redux-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/c2e61/setting-redux-1.png 148w,\n/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/08c14/setting-redux-1.png 295w,\n/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/setting-redux-1.png 544w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Actions</h2>\n<p>Inside the actions folder we add our actions creator, importing the constants we made.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/3edcd/setting-redux-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 20.802919708029197%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/fb8a0/setting-redux-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/1a291/setting-redux-2.png 148w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/2bc4a/setting-redux-2.png 295w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/fb8a0/setting-redux-2.png 590w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/3edcd/setting-redux-2.png 822w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>API</h2>\n<p>We’re going to use Redux Thunk for this, which </p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>We learned about Redux principles in very few texts, but to truly grasp it we need to create a project, we’re actually gonna do two, one will be a small project where we will use all the concepts we learned today and for async we will use Redux Thunk. For the other project we will use Redux Saga, Selectors and Models, all of these concepts we will learn them in another post before doing said project.</p>\n<p>See you on the next post.</p>\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>Eng Adrian Beria.</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to setup Redux","date":"February 20, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/9-setting-redux/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/10-redux-thunk/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}},"next":null}}